    "body": "The discussion in https://github.com/ipython/ipython/pull/9900 is pointed to from the README, and was indeed proactive and very helpful. But it only covers the case \"I'm installing IPython itself\".  Extending that effort with tips for the other projects which depend on IPython (and also have naive users doing source builds) is what I'm talking about here.\r\n\r\nA blog post about 6.0.0rc1 and its impact would be most welcome."
