    "author_association": "MEMBER",
    "body": "Hi @nealmcb,\r\n\r\nI'll let @takluyver and @carreau provide more details on the possibility of editing error messages/install messages on discontinuing 2.7 support beyond the IPython 5 LTS release.\r\n\r\n>It would be helpful to have more readily visible or even proactive advice on how to configure setup.py, pip, and other dependency-management systems for a wide variety of use cases. E.g. how to configure a project to depend on ipython 6 for supported python versions, but version 5 otherwise.\r\n\r\nWe can definitely look at the docs and README to further highlight Python 2 support and IPython 5 LTS.\r\n\r\n> A blog post about 6.0.0rc1 and its impact would be most welcome.\r\n\r\nThanks for the suggestion. We typically do blog posts for major releases and mailing list posts for release candidates.\r\n\r\nThanks!"
  },
