    "created_at": "2017-04-11T14:56:36Z",
    "updated_at": "2017-04-11T14:56:36Z",
    "author_association": "MEMBER",
    "body": "Many packages are only uploaded as source packages, and the setup script can ask for different dependencies depending on the environment (e.g. require x only on Windows, or only on Python 2). So you can't have a static list of all a packages dependencies in general.\r\n\r\nThere are better ways to handle conditional dependencies now - you can make a static list with 'environment markers' to filter which ones are used. If packages provide the information, PyPI can record dependencies (e.g. [astsearch](https://pypi.python.org/pypi/astsearch) shows the dependency on astcheck). But many packages don't."
  },
